1
00:00:00,020 --> 00:00:05,080
♪ Inside the state a city is built ♪

2
00:00:05,080 --> 00:00:10,190
♪ Where a benevolent emperor resides ♪

3
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:15,330
♪ Court officials are brave and able ♪

4
00:00:15,330 --> 00:00:22,750
♪ The empress is fair ♪

5
00:00:25,580 --> 00:00:30,710
♪ Princes died too young to ascend the throne ♪

6
00:00:30,710 --> 00:00:35,570
♪ Princesses are spoiled and fragile ♪

7
00:00:35,840 --> 00:00:40,270
♪ Commoners are also the emperor’s children ♪

8
00:00:40,830 --> 00:00:49,630
♪ All are living peacefully ♪

9
00:00:49,930 --> 00:00:54,280
♪ Wish I could live a day for myself ♪

10
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:59,380
♪ Follow my heart and ethics without distractions ♪

11
00:01:00,710 --> 00:01:03,400
♪ To be a good husband ♪

12
00:01:03,400 --> 00:01:05,970
♪ To be a caring father ♪

13
00:01:06,460 --> 00:01:10,110
♪ We were close when we first met ♪

14
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:14,710
♪ I hope I can control my desires ♪

15
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:20,060
♪ To be a worriless emperor and father ♪

16
00:01:21,120 --> 00:01:23,860
♪ Prudence tops all virtues ♪

17
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:26,480
♪ People build the state ♪

18
00:01:26,750 --> 00:01:30,020
= Held in the Lonely Castle =
♪ May the world be peaceful ♪

19
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:33,020
= Episode 19 =

20
00:01:47,660 --> 00:01:48,500
It’s 3 o’clock.

21
00:01:59,020 --> 00:02:00,700
After Deming died

22
00:02:01,260 --> 00:02:02,740
and Yuanhao succeeded his father’s title,

23
00:02:03,220 --> 00:02:05,260
he has been disrespectful.

24
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:09,020
His Majesty doesn’t want to start a war

25
00:02:09,580 --> 00:02:10,740
and treat him with tolerance and benevolence.

26
00:02:11,820 --> 00:02:14,100
But this made him worse.

27
00:02:15,660 --> 00:02:17,420
Now he’s even usurping the title of an emperor

28
00:02:17,420 --> 00:02:18,940
to disgrace our court.

29
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:20,500
I think

30
00:02:21,140 --> 00:02:22,460
I should propose to His Majesty

31
00:02:22,940 --> 00:02:25,540
to remove his title, his imperial name

32
00:02:25,940 --> 00:02:30,140
and condemn him for his misbehavior.

33
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:33,460
Remove his title and his name,
condemn him for his misbehavior?

34
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:54,620
The one who wrote a credential to us

35
00:02:55,540 --> 00:02:58,380
changed his name into Weiming Nangxiao

36
00:02:58,940 --> 00:03:00,500
claimed himself as the son of heaven,

37
00:03:01,140 --> 00:03:02,220
and called himself as an emperor.

38
00:03:02,340 --> 00:03:04,500
He takes culture as the foundation
and develops military power,

39
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:05,660
advocates laws, etiquettes,
benevolence and filial duties.

40
00:03:07,940 --> 00:03:08,660
Prime Minister Zhang,

41
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:11,540
what are you going to tell His Majesty

42
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:13,020
to remove?

43
00:03:13,540 --> 00:03:14,980
The title and imperial name

44
00:03:14,980 --> 00:03:16,260
that have been thrown away like trash?

45
00:03:19,580 --> 00:03:20,500
Su Shunqin,

46
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:23,180
you are so uncourteous!

47
00:03:23,420 --> 00:03:24,140
Courteous?

48
00:03:25,100 --> 00:03:27,340
We’ve been courteous for 25 years,

49
00:03:27,620 --> 00:03:30,140
holding a respectful
and tolerant attitude to outside.

50
00:03:31,020 --> 00:03:32,020
How dare you be so reckless!

51
00:03:37,940 --> 00:03:39,180
People in the West

52
00:03:39,900 --> 00:03:41,020
are the reckless ones!

53
00:03:41,780 --> 00:03:43,540
And they’ve been reckless

54
00:03:43,540 --> 00:03:44,580
not since they wrote the credential.

55
00:03:46,340 --> 00:03:48,460
The credential just reached to us,

56
00:03:49,060 --> 00:03:50,700
but haven’t they been reckless

57
00:03:50,820 --> 00:03:52,180
since long ago?

58
00:03:52,460 --> 00:03:53,540
Everyone here

59
00:03:53,540 --> 00:03:54,980
and His Majesty just learned

60
00:03:55,100 --> 00:03:56,100
their disrespectful

61
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:57,340
and reckless

62
00:03:57,420 --> 00:03:58,500
actions?

63
00:04:00,060 --> 00:04:01,740
Your Majesty.

64
00:04:01,860 --> 00:04:04,700
Your Majesty.

65
00:04:19,860 --> 00:04:21,100
When I was young,

66
00:04:21,860 --> 00:04:23,460
you taught me classics of literature

67
00:04:24,220 --> 00:04:25,300
and the ways to rule a country.

68
00:04:27,380 --> 00:04:28,140
You told me

69
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:30,540
Mencius once told King Hui of Liang

70
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:34,580
people always want

71
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:37,900
an emperor who’s not bloodthirsty and warlike.

72
00:04:39,740 --> 00:04:41,060
With such a benevolent emperor,

73
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:43,420
all the people will return

74
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:45,140
and the whole world can be unified.

75
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:48,020
All of you

76
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:50,980
are followers of Confucius and Mencius.

77
00:04:51,580 --> 00:04:53,140
Some of them are eminent scholars.

78
00:04:53,900 --> 00:04:56,100
Now I’d like to ask

79
00:04:57,220 --> 00:04:58,700
if what Mencius said

80
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:02,180
is correct.

81
00:05:02,980 --> 00:05:04,020
If it’s not,

82
00:05:04,860 --> 00:05:06,220
why do you always quote it

83
00:05:06,340 --> 00:05:07,940
when you are suggesting me

84
00:05:08,020 --> 00:05:09,020
to be benevolent?

85
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:10,180
If it is correct,

86
00:05:10,940 --> 00:05:11,660
then I

87
00:05:12,740 --> 00:05:14,580
never want to see people dying

88
00:05:14,700 --> 00:05:15,980
from the war,

89
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:17,700
But why didn’t I win

90
00:05:17,700 --> 00:05:18,980
the Tangut people’s heart

91
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:20,620
but breed some unmerciful evils?

92
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:28,060
I think

93
00:05:29,300 --> 00:05:31,700
what Mencius said is right.

94
00:05:32,340 --> 00:05:33,380
People always

95
00:05:33,420 --> 00:05:35,100
want to live in peace.

96
00:05:35,220 --> 00:05:36,180
They want no war.

97
00:05:37,060 --> 00:05:39,460
They love emperors who are not bloodthirsty.

98
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:41,020
But in the end

99
00:05:41,020 --> 00:05:41,980
what they need

100
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,620
is an emperor that can protect them.

101
00:05:43,860 --> 00:05:45,180
They will only submit themselves to

102
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:46,700
an emperor who can deter bloodthirsty people

103
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:47,940
and gain their allegiance,

104
00:05:47,940 --> 00:05:49,460
not an emperor who steps back

105
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:53,740
from them.

106
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:58,020
Mr. Su just gave a perfect answer.

107
00:06:08,580 --> 00:06:09,820
The Imperial Academy, draft the decree immediately.

108
00:06:10,460 --> 00:06:11,500
Send Imperial Guards

109
00:06:11,700 --> 00:06:12,700
to suppress the traitors.

110
00:06:13,220 --> 00:06:13,589
I

111
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:15,780
will lead the army myself.

112
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:27,740
Yuanhao is just bluffing.

113
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:29,460
We shouldn’t be worried.

114
00:06:29,660 --> 00:06:31,580
Even if he sent troops cross the border,

115
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:33,500
he’s like an ant trying to shake a giant tree.

116
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,540
How can Your Majesty lower yourself

117
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:37,460
to fight against a traitor in person?

118
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,220
Your Majesty shouldn’t

119
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:40,620
risk your life for that.

120
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:41,780
Please reconsider it.

121
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:43,300
Please reconsider it.

122
00:06:44,020 --> 00:06:45,620
Please reconsider it.

123
00:06:48,020 --> 00:06:48,740
Your Majesty,

124
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:50,900
the mistake was made in the past.

125
00:06:51,140 --> 00:06:53,140
= Cai Xiang, courtesy name Junmo =
Now Your Majesty wants to lead the army in person

126
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:54,940
for the unbearable humiliation,

127
00:06:54,940 --> 00:06:56,500
this is not correcting the mistake,

128
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,660
but making more mistakes.

129
00:06:59,500 --> 00:07:00,900
The betrayal of Yuanhao

130
00:07:00,940 --> 00:07:02,940
is not caused by your connivance.

131
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,260
Ever since the war in Tang dynasty,

132
00:07:05,620 --> 00:07:06,540
the Tangut people

133
00:07:06,540 --> 00:07:08,580
gradually gained the control of the west
of the Yellow River.

134
00:07:09,260 --> 00:07:10,540
Since our first emperor’s reign,

135
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:12,940
we’ve been trying to regain the region.

136
00:07:13,180 --> 00:07:14,300
But no matter what measures we’ve taken,

137
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:15,140
soft or hard,

138
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:16,300
we never succeed.

139
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:17,700
Your Majesty follow the policies

140
00:07:18,020 --> 00:07:19,420
to Xixia from the late Emperor

141
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:20,220
and didn’t...

142
00:07:20,220 --> 00:07:22,300
In 1004 A.D., Jiqian suddenly deceased,

143
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:24,180
which caused chaos inside of the Tangut people.

144
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:26,660
General Cao Wei
proposed to launch an attack to the west

145
00:07:26,660 --> 00:07:28,260
to retake the land.

146
00:07:29,580 --> 00:07:32,220
But the late Emperor didn’t take his advice

147
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:34,340
because it was not appropriate to attack them

148
00:07:34,340 --> 00:07:34,980
when they were still in mourning.

149
00:07:35,180 --> 00:07:38,300
Since then,
Deming gradually gained the control of the west.

150
00:07:38,460 --> 00:07:41,780
Your Majesty did follow the previous policy

151
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:43,860
and didn’t correct it.

152
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,780
Scholar Cai, are you criticizing the mistake

153
00:07:47,780 --> 00:07:49,620
made in the past

154
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,540
or giving His Majesty advice

155
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:52,900
about what is happening now?

156
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:54,980
Why should we avoid mentioning things
that happened before?

157
00:07:56,380 --> 00:07:57,580
Reviewing things in the past

158
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:58,380
is the foundation

159
00:07:58,380 --> 00:07:59,860
of discussing current things.

160
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:05,700
Your Majesty,

161
00:08:05,940 --> 00:08:07,620
you say you want to lead the troop yourself

162
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:08,940
to correct the wrong decision out of fear of war

163
00:08:08,980 --> 00:08:10,340
with the most courageous behavior.

164
00:08:10,820 --> 00:08:11,540
But this

165
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:12,660
just shows you do not have the courage

166
00:08:13,020 --> 00:08:14,740
to face the previous mistake.

167
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:26,220
Who said

168
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:28,380
it’s not allowed to comment on the past?

169
00:08:29,980 --> 00:08:31,420
You are all gathered here,

170
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:34,140
did you hear from any eunuch saying that

171
00:08:36,660 --> 00:08:38,580
those who comment on the past are guilty

172
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,300
and shall be demoted or killed?

173
00:09:06,860 --> 00:09:08,980
You can say anything you want

174
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:10,820
whether the decision made before is right or wrong,

175
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:12,540
merciful or cowardly.

176
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:13,620
You will not be punished for that.

177
00:09:27,140 --> 00:09:28,660
Put this in the hall of Cabinet.

178
00:09:30,660 --> 00:09:32,020
This is what I said

179
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:32,980
written down on the paper.

180
00:09:33,380 --> 00:09:35,820
If any of you who want to discuss
about the mistakes I

181
00:09:36,060 --> 00:09:37,260
or the late Emperor made

182
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:39,340
are suppressed by superiors or ministers,

183
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:40,740
you can use this to refute.

184
00:09:56,060 --> 00:09:56,740
What’s wrong?

185
00:09:58,740 --> 00:09:59,820
Giving advice against the will of the Emperor

186
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:03,420
shows your uprightness better

187
00:10:03,540 --> 00:10:04,500
than do what as you are told to?

188
00:10:08,860 --> 00:10:10,660
You can say whatever you want about

189
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:12,500
my merits and demerits as an emperor.

190
00:10:12,900 --> 00:10:13,900
Record everything from your discussion

191
00:10:14,420 --> 00:10:16,100
into the national document of our country.

192
00:10:16,980 --> 00:10:18,140
But first thing first.

193
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:21,580
The Imperial Academy shall write
the decree of me leading the troop myself

194
00:10:21,660 --> 00:10:22,860
to the world.

195
00:10:22,980 --> 00:10:24,260
Once the decree is finished,

196
00:10:24,780 --> 00:10:27,660
you can continue to discuss

197
00:10:27,660 --> 00:10:28,660
the merits and demerits of the past.

198
00:10:29,540 --> 00:10:32,380
If you do get some insights,

199
00:10:33,260 --> 00:10:34,740
and ask me to write the Letter of Introspection,

200
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:36,340
I shall do that.

201
00:10:41,060 --> 00:10:41,820
Well,

202
00:10:43,765 --> 00:10:44,629
well…

203
00:11:37,260 --> 00:11:38,900
Now let’s go to practice.

204
00:11:39,780 --> 00:11:41,980
This dance shows power and prestige.

205
00:11:42,460 --> 00:11:43,540
We girls

206
00:11:43,540 --> 00:11:45,180
need to act like warriors.

207
00:11:46,180 --> 00:11:47,220
The rebellion of the Tangut

208
00:11:47,220 --> 00:11:48,380
must annoy His Majesty.

209
00:11:49,220 --> 00:11:51,020
We can’t make any contributions

210
00:11:51,940 --> 00:11:53,340
other than boost the morale with our dance

211
00:11:53,340 --> 00:11:54,380
and relieve His Majesty’s worry.

212
00:11:55,580 --> 00:11:56,580
His Majesty's leading the troop himself

213
00:11:56,580 --> 00:11:57,820
can surely boost the morale

214
00:11:58,060 --> 00:12:00,260
and make every soldier brave.

215
00:12:00,740 --> 00:12:02,540
We do admire it.

216
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:04,740
But this is not a small thing.

217
00:12:04,740 --> 00:12:05,820
It should be discussed thoroughly

218
00:12:05,980 --> 00:12:09,220
instead of announcing it right away.

219
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:10,940
I want to lead the troop

220
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,180
just to boost the morale?

221
00:12:15,660 --> 00:12:16,580
Let me ask you,

222
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:20,220
why do I fear the war?

223
00:12:39,140 --> 00:12:40,220
Yes, you are right.

224
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,460
I fear the war,

225
00:12:45,060 --> 00:12:45,900
because I don’t want to lose,

226
00:12:46,820 --> 00:12:49,380
waste the finance of people
and destroy people’s life.

227
00:12:50,900 --> 00:12:52,260
People die

228
00:12:52,300 --> 00:12:53,900
but no fame for winning the battle is gained

229
00:12:54,540 --> 00:12:56,140
but only the humiliation of losing the war.

230
00:12:58,620 --> 00:12:59,460
Su Zimei,

231
00:13:01,100 --> 00:13:04,020
do you know why I fear it?

232
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:07,660
First,

233
00:13:09,140 --> 00:13:10,220
we don’t have enough good horses.

234
00:13:10,780 --> 00:13:13,060
Our cavalry is not as good as theirs.

235
00:13:13,860 --> 00:13:15,340
That’s exactly the consequence of

236
00:13:15,340 --> 00:13:16,620
the Tangut taking control of the west

237
00:13:16,980 --> 00:13:18,660
where we breed good horses for generations.

238
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:20,900
Second,

239
00:13:26,660 --> 00:13:27,580
civil officials are controlling the army

240
00:13:28,300 --> 00:13:30,580
while generals who are leading the troops
do not have the power.

241
00:13:30,780 --> 00:13:32,540
During the war,
eunuch officials supervise the army,

242
00:13:32,780 --> 00:13:33,580
war strategies

243
00:13:36,140 --> 00:13:37,940
often come from the Capital,
far away from the battlefield.

244
00:13:39,780 --> 00:13:41,900
Then why did Emperor Taizu reformed the army

245
00:13:42,500 --> 00:13:45,300
and took the power away from generals?

246
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:51,820
In Tang,

247
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:53,500
the right of troop deployment

248
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:54,860
is always in the generals’ hand.

249
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,820
It might be good for protecting
and expanding our territory,

250
00:13:57,820 --> 00:14:00,100
but ultimately caused the Chaos of Vassal Towns.

251
00:14:01,580 --> 00:14:02,820
The prosperity of Tang

252
00:14:03,540 --> 00:14:05,220
was ruined in warfare,

253
00:14:05,300 --> 00:14:06,620
followed by years of

254
00:14:06,620 --> 00:14:07,580
tangled fight,

255
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:09,060
hunger, disease,

256
00:14:09,580 --> 00:14:10,700
warlords and loot.

257
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:13,020
People had no way of making a living.

258
00:14:13,980 --> 00:14:15,700
Mr. Su, do you agree?

259
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:17,580
Yes.

260
00:14:19,340 --> 00:14:22,380
Emperor Taizu learned from the history

261
00:14:23,020 --> 00:14:24,020
and separated the right of leadership
from deployment

262
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:26,140
to prevent the internal conflicts

263
00:14:26,580 --> 00:14:29,100
so that the court won’t be threatened by generals.

264
00:14:29,340 --> 00:14:30,540
But once we are having war with foreign forces,

265
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:31,900
generals at the battlefield

266
00:14:32,180 --> 00:14:33,940
can’t deploy their army timely

267
00:14:35,620 --> 00:14:37,340
and the supervisor of army is
not well-informed of the war situation.

268
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:38,140
After it is reported

269
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:39,700
through all the levels of ranking

270
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:41,740
the situation on the battlefield has changed.

271
00:14:46,140 --> 00:14:48,980
But that wasn’t a problem for Emperor Taizu

272
00:14:49,380 --> 00:14:50,340
when he made that rule.

273
00:14:51,540 --> 00:14:52,300
Because

274
00:14:53,580 --> 00:14:54,500
in his reign,

275
00:14:55,460 --> 00:14:56,660
he led the army himself

276
00:14:57,260 --> 00:14:59,220
for almost all the wars,

277
00:14:59,300 --> 00:15:00,180
and made all the decisions right
at the battlefield.

278
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:03,900
The shortcomings of our army system

279
00:15:04,340 --> 00:15:05,900
can only be made up in one way.

280
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:07,380
That is

281
00:15:08,260 --> 00:15:09,340
